org.apache.cayenne.access

Class ToManyList

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.cayenne.util.RelationshipFault
      • org.apache.cayenne.util.PersistentObjectList
        • org.apache.cayenne.access.ToManyList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable, Collection, List, PersistentObjectCollection, ValueHolder

    public class ToManyList
extends PersistentObjectList
implements Serializable
    A list that holds objects for to-many relationships. All operations, except for resolving the list from DB, are not synchronized. The safest way to implement custom synchronization is to synchronize on parent ObjectStore.
    See Also:
